title: For Sale:  Custom Bulgarian AK-105
postcontent: Looking to sell this Bulgarian AK-105 that I've been sitting on for a while. This started out with a 74u LLC. receiver that I got from a guy that messed up drilling the center scope rail hole and general rough handling. The messed up hole doesn't effect anything and you can't see it unless you look inside right at the rivet. I then used a bunch of spare parts to finish it off. The barrel was shortened and then the Damage Ind. flash hider was permanently attached via blind pin and weld. You can see the weld spot. Now for the bad. Normally, I do all of my own parkerizing, but this time I was leaving for vacation and wanted to have it done by the time I got back. So I dropped it off at a local "smith" to blast and park. Well, he did a shit job and it doesn't look good in my opinion. Now, some of my friends said it's not that bad, but to me it's unacceptable. I ended up not having to pay for the work and therefore will not add the cost of reginishing into the sale price. The park will do what it was intended, just not look good while doing it. Looking to get $1,200 shipped for the rifle. No magazines are included. This price is purely what's in it parts wise, maybe less, in fact, and does not include my time and materials in building it. I'll get better pics when I actually have some good light out.
